{% extends 'src/partials/layout.njk'%}
{% block content %}
<header style="width: 100%; height: 907px; background-image: url('/pussiveskiasi.jpg'); background-size: cover; background-position: center; background-color: red;">
  <div style="display: flex;">
    <h1 class="font-beardbone text-left" style="user-select: none; font-size: 300px; color: white; padding-left: 274px; padding-top: 289px">PÜSSI</h1>
    <h1 class="font-beardbone text-right" style="user-select: none; font-size: 300px; color: white; padding-left: 274px; padding-top: 289px;">VESKI</h1>
    <img src="/Wlogo.png" alt="Wlogo" style="user-select: none; width: 600px; height: 600px; position: absolute; top: 160px; left: 660px; z-index: 1; opacity: 0.4;">
  </div>
</header>
<main>
  <section style="margin-top: 100px; padding-bottom: 100px;">
      <svg style="position: absolute; margin-top: 70px; right: 0px;" height="262px" width="254px">
        <use href="/revolverhalved.svg" fill="#CB2729" height="262px" width="254px"/>
      </svg>
      <svg style="position: absolute; margin-top: 70px; left: 0px;" height="262px" width="254px">
        <use href="/revolverhalvedflip.svg" fill="#CB2729" height="262px" width="254px"/>
      </svg>
    <div>
      <div style="padding-bottom: 50px; display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; position: relative; gap: 6px; width: 100%;">
        <svg width="500" height="4" style="flex-shrink: 0;">
          <rect width="500" height="4" fill="#CB2729"/>
        </svg>
        <h2 class="font-beardbone text-center" style="font-size: 128px; color: #CB2729; margin: 0; flex-shrink: 0;">HISTORY</h2>
        <svg width="500" height="4" style="flex-shrink: 0;">
          <rect width="500" height="4" fill="#CB2729"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div style="gap: 184px; display: flex; padding-inline: 274px;">
        <article style="width: 328px;">
          <header style="padding-bottom: 10px;">
            <h3 class="text-left font-extrabold" style="font-size: 24px">Creation of Püssi veski</h3>
            <p class="font-light" style="font-size: 20px; color: #D89C00;">1974 - 1986</p>
          </header>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; color: #151415;">
            Püssi Veski was established in 1974 by a group of passionate individuals who shared a vision of creating a unique and welcoming space for the community. The founders, inspired by the rich history of Püssi, aimed to blend tradition with modernity, resulting in a venue that would become a beloved local landmark. <br>
            Over the years, Püssi Veski has evolved, adapting to the changing needs and tastes of its patrons while remaining true to its roots. The dedication to quality and service has made it a staple in the community, attracting visitors from near and far.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article style="width: 328px; padding-top: 150px;">
          <header style="padding-bottom: 10px;">
            <h3 class="text-left font-extrabold" style="font-size: 24px">Creating guns in Püssi</h3>
            <p class="font-light" style="font-size: 20px; color: #D89C00;">1987 - 2001</p>
          </header>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; color: #151415;">
            In the late 1980s, Püssi Veski expanded its offerings to include a unique line of handcrafted firearms. This decision was driven by the growing demand for high-quality, artisanal weapons among collectors and enthusiasts. The guns produced at Püssi Veski quickly gained a reputation for their craftsmanship and attention to detail, attracting buyers from across the region. <br>
            The transition from a traditional venue to a firearms manufacturer marked a significant shift in Püssi Veski's history, showcasing its adaptability and commitment to excellence.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article style="width: 328px;">
          <header style="padding-bottom: 10px;">
            <h3 class="text-left font-extrabold" style="font-size: 24px">New management</h3>
            <p class="font-light" style="font-size: 20px; color: #D89C00;">2002 - Today</p>
          </header>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; color: #151415;">
            In 2002, Püssi Veski underwent a significant management change, bringing in a new team dedicated to revitalizing the brand while preserving its heritage. The new management focused on enhancing the customer experience, introducing innovative products, and expanding the venue's offerings. <br>
            Today, Püssi Veski stands as a testament to its rich history and evolution, continuing to serve the community with pride and excellence. The commitment to quality and tradition remains at the heart of everything they do, ensuring that Püssi Veski will continue to be a cherished part of the local culture for years to come.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section>
      <svg style="position:absolute; margin-top: 35px; left: -242px; z-index: -1;" height="304px" width="1530px">
        <use href="/shotgun.svg" fill="#CB2729" height="304px" width="1530px"/>
      </svg>
    <div style="padding-bottom: 50px;">
      <h2 class="font-beardbone text-left font-outline-8" style="padding-inline: 274px; font-size: 128px; color: #CB2729; margin: 0; flex-shrink: 0;">HISTORIC FIGURES</h2>
    </div>
    <div style="padding-inline: 274px; padding-bottom: 100px; display: flex; gap: 194px; justify-content: center;">
      <article style="align-items: center; width: 328px;">
        <header style="padding-bottom: 10px;">
          <img src="/nedkelly.jpg" alt="Ned Killy" style="width: 328px; height: 328px; border-radius: 100%; object-fit: cover; margin-bottom: 20px;">
          <h3 class="text-center font-beardbone" style="font-size: 32px">Ned Kelly</h3>
        </header>
        <p class="text-center" style="font-size: 16px; color: #151415;">
          Ned Kelly was the visionary behind the creation of Püssi Veski, establishing it as a cornerstone of the local community. His leadership and dedication to quality set the standard for generations to come.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article style="align-items: center; width: 328px;">
        <header style="padding-bottom: 10px;">
          <img src="/bassreeves.jpg" alt="Bass Pro" style="width: 328px; height: 328px; border-radius: 100%; object-fit: cover; margin-bottom: 20px;">
          <h3 class="text-center font-beardbone" style="font-size: 32px">Bass Reeves</h3>
        </header>
        <p class="text-center" style="font-size: 16px; color: #151415;">
          Bass Reeves was a legendary lawman and the first black deputy Estonian Marshal west of the Püssi River. His fearless pursuit of justice and unwavering integrity made him a symbol of courage and resilience in the face of adversity.
        </p>
      </article><article style="align-items: center; width: 328px;">
        <header style="padding-bottom: 10px;">
          <img src="/buffalobill.jpg" alt="Buffer my bill" style="width: 328px; height: 328px; border-radius: 100%; object-fit: cover; margin-bottom: 20px;">
          <h3 class="text-center font-beardbone" style="font-size: 32px">"Buffalo" Bill Cody</h3>
        </header>
        <p class="text-center" style="font-size: 16px; color: #151415;">
          "Buffalo" Bill Cody was a legendary figure of the Estonian East, known for his Wild West shows that celebrated the frontier spirit. His larger-than-life persona and showmanship captivated audiences, leaving an indelible mark on Estonian culture.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section style="background-color: #CB2729; padding-top: 100px; padding-bottom: 105px; color: white; position: relative; overflow: hidden;">
    <div style="width: hug; padding-inline: 274px; z-index: 1; position: relative;">
      <h2 class="font-beardbone text-left" style="font-size: 128px; margin: 0; flex-shrink: 0;">Attractions</h2>
      <p class="font-khula text-left" style="font-size: 16px; padding-bottom: 50px; width: 541px"> 
        Püssi Veski offers a range of attractions that showcase the rich history and culture of the region. From guided tours of the historic site to interactive exhibits that highlight the craftsmanship behind our artisanal firearms, there is something for everyone to enjoy.  
      </p>
      <div>
        <article style="width: 328px; padding-bottom: 50px;">
          <header>
            <h3 class="text-left font-extrabold" style="font-size: 24px">Tours</h3>
            <p class="font-light" style="font-size: 20px;">E-R 10:00 - 20:00</p>
          </header>
          <content>
            <p style="font-size: 16px; padding-bottom: 40px">
              Explore the wonderous landscape of Ida Virumaa and experience the culture of Püssi for yourself in groups of 10.
            </p>
            <btn class="outline outline-white outline-2" style="color: white; padding: 15px 30px; font-size: 16px; border-radius: 30px">
              READ MORE
            </btn>
          </content>
        </article>
        <article style="width: 328px;">
          <header>
            <h3 class="text-left font-extrabold" style="font-size: 24px">Shooting range</h3>
            <p class="font-light" style="font-size: 20px;">K-R 15:00 - 20:00</p>
          </header>
          <content>
            <p style="font-size: 16px; padding-bottom: 40px">
              Try out a wide variety of rifles, revolvers, derringers, and shotguns made right here in Püssi veski.
            </p>
            <btn class="outline outline-white outline-2" style="color: white; padding: 15px 30px; font-size: 16px; border-radius: 30px">
              READ MORE
            </btn>
          </content>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
    <svg style="position: absolute; bottom: 0; left: -300; width: 200%; z-index: 0;" height="557px" width="1945px">
      <defs>
        <linearGradient id="landscape-gradient" x1="0" y1="0" x2="1" y2="0">
          <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#CB2729"/>
          <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#770000"/>
        </linearGradient>
      </defs>
      <use href="/landscape.svg" fill="url(#landscape-gradient)" height="557px" width="1945px"/>
    </svg>
    <div id="auto-scroll-gallery" style="position: absolute; top: 0; right: 0; height: 100%; width: 602px; overflow-y: auto; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0; z-index: 2; border-radius: 0; padding: 0; scrollbar-width: none;">
      <img src="/derringer.jpg" alt="Derringer" style="width: 100%; height: 602px; width: 602px; object-fit: cover; border-radius: 0;">
      <img src="/winchester.jpg" alt="Winchester" style="width: 100%; height: 602px; width: 602px; object-fit: cover; border-radius: 0;">
      <img src="/twinrevolvers.jpg" alt="Twin Revolvers" style="width: 100%; height: 602px; width: 602px; object-fit: cover; border-radius: 0;">
      <img src="/derringersg.jpg" alt="Derringersg" style="width: 100%; height: 602px; width: 602px; object-fit: cover; border-radius: 0;">
    </div>
    <script>
      (function() {
      const gallery = document.getElementById('auto-scroll-gallery');
      let scrollStep = 1;
      let direction = 1;
      function autoScroll() {
      if (!gallery) return;
      if (direction === 1 && gallery.scrollTop + gallery.clientHeight >= gallery.scrollHeight) {
      direction = -1;
      } else if (direction === -1 && gallery.scrollTop <= 0) {
      direction = 1;
      }
      gallery.scrollTop += scrollStep * direction;
      }
      setInterval(autoScroll, 20);
      })();
    </script>
  </section>
</main>
{% endblock %}